verses.roman:
milana-sthāne āsi' prabhure nā mililā
rājapatha-prānte dūre paḍiyā rahilā

synonyms: milana-sthāne—in the meeting place; āsi'—coming; prabhure—unto Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; nā—not; mililā—did meet; rājapatha-prānte—on the side of the common road; dūre—at a distant place; paḍiyā—falling flat; rahilā—remained.
translation: Haridāsa Ṭhākura did not come to the Lord's meeting place but remained fallen flat on the common road at a distance.
